<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/22.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister to China</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Legation at Panama reports that the Government of Panama on the 17th
                            instant revoked the exequatur of the Chinese Consul General on the
                            ground of encouraging the Chinese not to comply with the law requiring
                            registration of Chinese. The Legation states that although the period of
                            registration expired September 15 without the Chinese complying with the
                            law, the Government of Panama has not applied coercive measures. Chinese
                            Chargé d’Affaires here advised.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>